parameter.comment:
23405.5 kg of Zr(Hf)Cl4 (zirconium tetrachloride bundled with hafnium) with a composition of 98.4% ZrCl4 is entering the extractive distillation column. The recovery rate of ZrCl4 is 85% that ends up in the bottom stream after the recovery of the salts in stripper unit, thus producing 19576.36 kg of high-purity ZrCl4. As a result, approximately 1.1956 kg of Zr(Hf)Cl4 is required for the production of 1 kg of high-purity ZrCl4.
Reference: Minh, L. Q., Long, N. V. D., Duong, P. L. T., Jung, Y., Bahadori, A., & Lee, M. (2015). Design of an Extractive Distillation Column for the Environmentally Benign Separation of Zirconium and Hafnium Tetrachloride for Nuclear Power Reactor Applications. Energies, 8(9), 10354-10369)

parameter.comment: This parameter is applied to convert the the exhaust emissions of a passenger car fueled by natural gas. The differences with conventional petrol car are in terms of fuel consumption and emission factors. The natural gas fuel consumption is calculated in m³ CNG per vehicle-km as the petrol consumption multiplied by a multiplication factor, 1.077. Conversion for m³ to tonnes then happens via the fuel density (0.734 kg/m³ at 1 atm).
